# Task 1 – Project Understanding

## Client
Australian Federal Government

## Project
Design of a Secure Online Voting System

## Project Context

The Australian Federal Government plans to introduce a secure online voting system to improve accessibility and efficiency in elections.

Accenture has been engaged as a technology consulting partner to analyze system requirements and design the core components of the platform.

The system must ensure security, transparency, and reliability while allowing voters to participate digitally.

---

## Key Objectives

• Provide a secure platform for online voting  
• Manage voter eligibility and authentication  
• Enable ballot creation and administration  
• Allow voters to cast votes through a digital portal  
• Store votes securely and generate election results  
• Maintain audit logs for election transparency  

---

## Key System Modules

### Secure Authentication Engine
Handles identity verification and secure access for voters and administrators.

### Voter Maintenance
Maintains voter records and eligibility information.

### Ballot Administration
Allows administrators to create, configure, and publish ballots for elections.

### Voter Portal
Provides the interface where voters can view ballots and submit their votes.

### Notification Engine
Sends notifications to voters regarding elections and voting deadlines.

### Ballot Tabulation
Processes votes and generates election results.

### Audit Reporting
Tracks system activity to ensure election transparency and compliance.

---

## Consulting Objective

The role of the consulting team is to analyze system requirements and design the architecture of the voting platform.

This project focuses on:

• Understanding the business problem  
• Gathering functional requirements  
• Designing system components  
• Creating Agile user stories for development teams
